title: Wiley Series in Corrosion [Updated at 2016.02.14]
description:
The books in the Wiley Series in Corrosion summarize the current status and major trends in topical areas of corrosion science and engineering, including both fundamental science and applications of current technology to control corrosion, reduce risk, and manage integrity in engineering practice. The books in this Series will help the reader to understand, at a fundamental level, the complexities of corrosion and to develop corrosion control measures. 

The Series provides a major resource for: 
Industrial and academic corrosion scientists who carry out fundamental and applied research, 
Engineers who develop strategies for managing corrosion, 
University professors and students who include corrosion in their research and studies, 
Instructors and their students in specialized short courses, and 
Readers with a general interest in the specific topics of corrosion that are addressed in the Series
